{"id":16374,"title":"The management of central venous catheters and infection control: is it time to change our approach?","abstract":"Catheter related bloodstream infections (CR-BSIs) can lead to a number of serious conditions for the patient, including death. There is much recent evidence both in the UK and abroad which identifies the sources of CR-BSIs, yet they continue to occur. This article seeks to review some of the current evidence in relation to the prevention of CR-BSIs at insertion point.","date":"2014-07-10","categories":"Bacterial Infections and Mycoses","split":"train","url":"http://www.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/pubmed/25007476","annotations":[{"name":"Infection","weight":0.762559,"wikipedia_article":"http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Infection"},{"name":"Circulatory system","weight":0.728515,"wikipedia_article":"http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Circulatory_system"},{"name":"Death","weight":0.672208,"wikipedia_article":"http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Death"},{"name":"Catheter","weight":0.668585,"wikipedia_article":"http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Catheter"},{"name":"Patient","weight":0.615997,"wikipedia_article":"http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Patient"},{"name":"Sepsis","weight":0.579861,"wikipedia_article":"http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Sepsis"},{"name":"United Kingdom","weight":0.424789,"wikipedia_article":"http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/United_Kingdom"},{"name":"Vein","weight":0.418781,"wikipedia_article":"http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Vein"},{"name":"Preventive medicine","weight":0.372176,"wikipedia_article":"http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Preventive_medicine"},{"name":"Central venous catheter","weight":0.230989,"wikipedia_article":"http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Central_venous_catheter"},{"name":"Infection control","weight":0.0891887,"wikipedia_article":"http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Infection_control"},{"name":"Lead","weight":0.0805305,"wikipedia_article":"http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Lead"},{"name":"Management","weight":0.0370044,"wikipedia_article":"http://en.wikipedia.org/wik